events.name: Miami Heat at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges scored 28 points, Josh Hart tied a franchise record with his eighth triple-double this season and the New York Knicks beat Miami 116-95 on Monday night, sending the Heat to their first eight-game losing streak of coach Erik Spoelstra's...
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks storm back to beat Miami 116-95 and send Heat to their 8th straight loss

headlines.description: — Jalen Green and Jabari Smith Jr. had 30 points apiece and the Houston Rockets rallied for a 144-137 overtime victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Monday night, extending their season-best winning streak to seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green, Smith each score 30, Rockets extend win streak to 7 games with 144-137 OT victory over 76ers

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 24 points and eight assists, and the Detroit Pistons routed the New Orleans Pelicans 127-81 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham, Pistons top New Orleans 127-81; Pelicans' Murphy out for season with shoulder injury

headlines.description: — Coby White scored 26 points and the Chicago Bulls beat Utah 111-97 on Monday night, sending the Jazz to their 10th straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coby White's 26 points leads balanced scoring effort as Bulls deal Jazz 10th straight loss, 111-97

events.name: Denver Nuggets at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Aaron Gordon scored a season-best 38 points, Russell Westbrook hit a crucial late 3-pointer and delivered a triple-double, and the undermanned Denver Nuggets missing their two main stars beat the Golden State Warriors 114-105 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Aaron Gordon, Russell Westbrook lead undermanned Nuggets past Warriors 114-105

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 27 points and led a second-quarter surge as the Phoenix Suns routed the Toronto Raptors 129-89 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker leads big 2nd quarter, Suns rout Raptors 129-89

headlines.description: — Malik Monk had 28 points and seven assists, and the Kings beat the Memphis Grizzlies 132-122 to end a four-game losing streak despite losing center Domantas Sabonis to a pair of injuries Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings lose Sabonis but hang on to beat Grizzlies 132-122

events.name: Washington Wizards at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 30 points and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Washington Wizards 112-97 on Monday night for their second consecutive victory following a five-game slide.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons scores 30 points as Trail Blazers beat last-place Wizards 112-97

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Austin Reaves scored 30 points and Luka Doncic had 21 points, 14 assists and nine rebounds in the Los Angeles Lakers' 125-109 victory over the San Antonio Spurs on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reaves scores 30 points, Doncic just misses triple-double in Lakers' 125-109 win over Spurs
